Pritunl Client
==============

Pritunl Client is an open source OpenVPN client.

Documentation and additional information are available from the
official project website:

  https://client.pritunl.com/


Service
-------

Before using Pritunl Client, the pritunl-client service must be
started. Without this service running, Pritunl Client will not work.

To start the service manually, run:

  /etc/rc.d/rc.pritunl-client start


Starting the Service at Boot
----------------------------

To start the pritunl-client service automatically at boot, add the
following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local:

  if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.pritunl-client ]; then
    # Start pritunl-client service:
    /etc/rc.d/rc.pritunl-client start
  fi


Stopping the Service at Shutdown
--------------------------------

To stop the pritunl-client service automatically during shutdown, add
the following to /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown:

  if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.pritunl-client ]; then
    # Stop pritunl-client service:
    /etc/rc.d/rc.pritunl-client stop
  fi


Slackware Package Notes
-----------------------

The package installer will add the necessary rc.d service commands to
both /etc/rc.d/rc.local and /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown.

The pritunl-client service must be started before using Pritunl Client.

For the Slackware package, `npm audit fix --force` is applied during the
build process. This differs from the upstream build procedure.
